In [[SLASH'EM]], many new '''[[golem]]s''' are introduced, including many golems from the [[Lethe patch]], and the golems retained from ''[[NetHack]]'' are made tougher as well.

{{todo|Describe differences between Lethe patch and SLASH'EM if any}}

==List of golems==
The following golems are added to SLASH'EM:

* {{monsymlink|wax golem}}
* {{monsymlink|plastic golem}}
* {{monsymlink|Frankenstein's Monster}}
* {{monsymlink|ruby golem}}
* {{monsymlink|diamond golem}}
* {{monsymlink|sapphire golem}}
* {{monsymlink|steel golem}}
* {{monsymlink|crystal golem}}

==Common traits==
In addition to their ''NetHack'' traits, all golems in SLASH'EM are given [[drain resistance]], making them immune to attacks such as the {{+ of|drain life}} spell and strikes from [[Stormbringer]]. The steel golem and the golems made of a type of [[gem]] have a [[weapon]] attack and an elemental [[breath]] weapon, and possess [[fire resistance]], [[cold resistance]] and [[shock resistance]] in addition to the [[poison resistance]] and [[sleep resistance]] that all golems have.

===Generation===
As in ''NetHack'', [[polymorph]]ing enough items of a particular [[material]] or set of materials has a chance of causing them to form a golem, destroying those items in the process;{{refsrc|zap.c|1186|version=SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F2|comment=<tt>create_polymon</tt> function}} this is not applied to all of the new golems added in SLASH'EM. Golems always generate with a set amount of [[HP]], and except for the flesh golem and Frankenstein's Monster, they [[Corpseless|do not leave corpses]] on death{{refsrc|mon.c|174|version=SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F2|name=deadgolem|comment=golem cases are handled as part of <tt>make_corpse</tt>}}{{refsrc|makemon.c|1477|version=SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F2|name=newgolem|comment=<tt>is_golem(ptr)</tt> calls <tt>golemhp</tt>}}{{refsrc|makemon.c|2239|version=SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F2|name=golemhp|comment=<tt>golemhp</tt>}} - many of these golems leave behind special [[death drop]]s as a "corpse" that are based on their material, and with some exceptions are dropped in the same circumstances as a regular corpse would be left.

